In this lesson, we'll be
focusing on three fundamental important examples, quantum teleportation, superdense coding and the CHSH game,

9
00:51.210 --> 00:57.060
which is also called the CHSH inequality and not always described as a game.

10
00:57.060 --> 01:03.570
These are not just random
examples meant to illustrate how quantum information works, they really are key
parts of the foundation

11
01:03.570 --> 01:12.300
of quantum information and
they arise in different and sometimes unexpected settings within quantum information
and computation.

12
