at a mathematical level.

18
01:53.130 --> 02:00.090
Before we get to the first
of the three examples, which is quantum teleportation, it's appropriate to first
introduce the characters,

19
02:00.090 --> 02:04.470
Alice and Bob, in case you're
not familiar with them.

20
02:04.470 --> 02:12.630
Alice and and Bob, are names
given to hypothetical entities or agents in systems, protocols, games,

21
02:12.630 --> 02:18.780
and really any other type of interaction you might wish to consider that involves the exchange of information.

22
02:18.780 --> 02:26.400
They first arose in the
context of cryptography in the 1970s, but the
convention to use these names in this way has become very common

23
02:26.400 --> 02:34.920
in a much broader context since then. The idea is that these
are very common names, at least in some parts of the world, and they start with the letters A and B,

24
02:34.920 --> 02:42.750
and it's also convenient
to refer to Alice and Bob using the pronouns, her and him just for the sake of brevity.

25
02:42.750 --> 02:49.170
We typically imagine that Alice and Bob are in different locations and that they have different
goals and different behaviors

26
02:49.170 --> 02:52.380
depending upon whatever it is that we're talking about.

27
02:52.380 --> 02:59.760
For example, if we're
talking about communication, meaning, the transmission of information, then we might decide
that Alice is the sender

28
02:59.760 --> 03:04.350
and Bob is the receiver
of whatever information is being transmitted.

29
03:04.350 --> 03:12.180
Sometimes Alice and Bob
cooperate, that's very typical, but sometimes they
compete or they might have different goals that may
or may not be consistent

30
03:12.180 --> 03:17.490
with one another, but this
all has to be made clear in the situation at hand.

31
03:17.490 --> 03:23.370
Of course, they represent abstractions and not necessarily actual human beings.

32
03:23.370 --> 03:30.870
We can also introduce
additional characters such as Charlie and
Diane or different names that represent different
personas such as Eve

33
03:30.870 --> 03:37.290
for an Eves Strapper or Mallory for someone behaving maliciously
depending upon the setting.

34
03:37.290 --> 03:43.470
In any case, we will see Alice and Bob in all three of the
examples that we'll discuss in this lesson and from time to time

35
03:43.470 --> 03:52.800
